&lt;p&gt;Looking at those two structures, I would suggest that there is some kind of strain that forms. If we look at the 1-bromobicyclo[3.3.1]nonane, we can see that there is no strain, and thus the Br atom is quite stable in this position. However, there is more strain when it comes to bicyclo[2.2.1]heptane. Strain means unstability, and as we know, chemistry does not like unstable things. Br will prefer to attack a different carbon that is more stable if it means that the bond will be more stable.&lt;/p&gt;
